47TEST(PreparedHeap, BasicsTest) {
48 WritePreparedTxnDB::PreparedHeap heap;
49 {
50 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
51 heap.push(14l);
52 // Test with one element
53 ASSERT_EQ(14l, heap.top());
54 heap.push(24l);
55 heap.push(34l);
56 // Test that old min is still on top
57 ASSERT_EQ(14l, heap.top());
58 heap.push(44l);
59 heap.push(54l);
60 heap.push(64l);
61 heap.push(74l);
62 heap.push(84l);
63 }
64 // Test that old min is still on top
65 ASSERT_EQ(14l, heap.top());
66 heap.erase(24l);
67 // Test that old min is still on top
68 ASSERT_EQ(14l, heap.top());
69 heap.erase(14l);
70 // Test that the new comes to the top after multiple erase
71 ASSERT_EQ(34l, heap.top());
72 heap.erase(34l);
73 // Test that the new comes to the top after single erase
74 ASSERT_EQ(44l, heap.top());
75 heap.erase(54l);
76 ASSERT_EQ(44l, heap.top());
77 heap.pop(); // pop 44l
78 // Test that the erased items are ignored after pop
79 ASSERT_EQ(64l, heap.top());
80 heap.erase(44l);
81 // Test that erasing an already popped item would work
82 ASSERT_EQ(64l, heap.top());
83 heap.erase(84l);
84 ASSERT_EQ(64l, heap.top());
85 {
86 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
87 heap.push(85l);
88 heap.push(86l);
89 heap.push(87l);
90 heap.push(88l);
91 heap.push(89l);
92 }
93 heap.erase(87l);
94 heap.erase(85l);
95 heap.erase(89l);
96 heap.erase(86l);
97 heap.erase(88l);
98 // Test top remains the same after a random order of many erases
99 ASSERT_EQ(64l, heap.top());
100 heap.pop();
101 // Test that pop works with a series of random pending erases
102 ASSERT_EQ(74l, heap.top());
103 ASSERT_FALSE(heap.empty());
104 heap.pop();
105 // Test that empty works
106 ASSERT_TRUE(heap.empty());
107}

109// This is a scenario reconstructed from a buggy trace. Test that the bug does
110// not resurface again.
111TEST(PreparedHeap, EmptyAtTheEnd) {
112 WritePreparedTxnDB::PreparedHeap heap;
113 {
114 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
115 heap.push(40l);
116 }
117 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
118 // Although not a recommended scenario, we must be resilient against erase
119 // without a prior push.
120 heap.erase(50l);
121 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
122 {
123 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
124 heap.push(60l);
125 }
126 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
127
128 heap.erase(60l);
129 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
130 heap.erase(40l);
131 ASSERT_TRUE(heap.empty());
132
133 {
134 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
135 heap.push(40l);
136 }
137 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
138 heap.erase(50l);
139 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
140 {
141 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
142 heap.push(60l);
143 }
144 ASSERT_EQ(40l, heap.top());
145
146 heap.erase(40l);
147 // Test that the erase has not emptied the heap (we had a bug doing that)
148 ASSERT_FALSE(heap.empty());
149 ASSERT_EQ(60l, heap.top());
150 heap.erase(60l);
151 ASSERT_TRUE(heap.empty());
152}

154// Generate random order of PreparedHeap access and test that the heap will be
155// successfully emptied at the end.
156TEST(PreparedHeap, Concurrent) {
157 const size_t t_cnt = 10;
158 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread t[t_cnt + 1];
159 WritePreparedTxnDB::PreparedHeap heap;
160 port::RWMutex prepared_mutex;
161 std::atomic<size_t> last;
162
163 for (size_t n = 0; n < 100; n++) {
164 last = 0;
165 t[0] = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread([&]() {
166 Random rnd(1103);
167 for (size_t seq = 1; seq <= t_cnt; seq++) {
168 // This is not recommended usage but we should be resilient against it.
169 bool skip_push = rnd.OneIn(5);
170 if (!skip_push) {
171 MutexLock ml(heap.push_pop_mutex());
172 std::this_thread::yield();
173 heap.push(seq);
174 last.store(seq);
175 }
176 }
177 });
178 for (size_t i = 1; i <= t_cnt; i++) {
179 t[i] =
180 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread([&heap, &prepared_mutex, &last, i]() {
181 auto seq = i;
182 do {
183 std::this_thread::yield();
184 } while (last.load() < seq);
185 WriteLock wl(&prepared_mutex);
186 heap.erase(seq);
187 });
188 }
189 for (size_t i = 0; i <= t_cnt; i++) {
190 t[i].join();
191 }
192 ASSERT_TRUE(heap.empty());
193 }
194}

196// Test that WriteBatchWithIndex correctly counts the number of sub-batches
197TEST(WriteBatchWithIndex, SubBatchCnt) {
198 ColumnFamilyOptions cf_options;
199 std::string cf_name = "two";
200 DB* db;
201 Options options;
202 options.create_if_missing = true;
203 const std::string dbname = test::PerThreadDBPath("transaction_testdb");
204 EXPECT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname, options));
205 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname, &db));
206 ColumnFamilyHandle* cf_handle = nullptr;
207 ASSERT_OK(db->CreateColumnFamily(cf_options, cf_name, &cf_handle));
208 WriteOptions write_options;
209 size_t batch_cnt = 1;
210 size_t save_points = 0;
211 std::vector<size_t> batch_cnt_at;
212 WriteBatchWithIndex batch(db->DefaultColumnFamily()->GetComparator(), 0, true,
213 0);
214 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, batch.SubBatchCnt());
215 batch_cnt_at.push_back(batch_cnt);
216 batch.SetSavePoint();
217 save_points++;
218 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(Slice("key"), Slice("value")));
219 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, batch.SubBatchCnt());
220 batch_cnt_at.push_back(batch_cnt);
221 batch.SetSavePoint();
222 save_points++;
223 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(Slice("key2"), Slice("value2")));
224 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, batch.SubBatchCnt());
225 // duplicate the keys
226 batch_cnt_at.push_back(batch_cnt);
227 batch.SetSavePoint();
228 save_points++;
229 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(Slice("key"), Slice("value3")));
230 batch_cnt++;
231 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, batch.SubBatchCnt());
232 // duplicate the 2nd key. It should not be counted duplicate since a
233 // sub-patch is cut after the last duplicate.
234 batch_cnt_at.push_back(batch_cnt);
235 batch.SetSavePoint();
236 save_points++;
237 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(Slice("key2"), Slice("value4")));
238 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, batch.SubBatchCnt());
239 // duplicate the keys but in a different cf. It should not be counted as
240 // duplicate keys
241 batch_cnt_at.push_back(batch_cnt);
242 batch.SetSavePoint();
243 save_points++;
244 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(cf_handle, Slice("key"), Slice("value5")));
245 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, batch.SubBatchCnt());
246
247 // Test that the number of sub-batches matches what we count with
248 // SubBatchCounter
249 std::map<uint32_t, const Comparator*> comparators;
250 comparators[0] = db->DefaultColumnFamily()->GetComparator();
251 comparators[cf_handle->GetID()] = cf_handle->GetComparator();
252 SubBatchCounter counter(comparators);
253 ASSERT_OK(batch.GetWriteBatch()->Iterate(&counter));
254 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt, counter.BatchCount());
255
256 // Test that RollbackToSavePoint will properly resets the number of
257 // sub-batches
258 for (size_t i = save_points; i > 0; i--) {
259 ASSERT_OK(batch.RollbackToSavePoint());
260 ASSERT_EQ(batch_cnt_at[i - 1], batch.SubBatchCnt());
261 }
262
263 // Test the count is right with random batches
264 {
265 const size_t TOTAL_KEYS = 20; // 20 ~= 10 to cause a few randoms
266 Random rnd(1131);
267 std::string keys[TOTAL_KEYS];
268 for (size_t k = 0; k < TOTAL_KEYS; k++) {
269 int len = static_cast<int>(rnd.Uniform(50));
270 keys[k] = test::RandomKey(&rnd, len);
271 }
272 for (size_t i = 0; i < 1000; i++) { // 1000 random batches
273 WriteBatchWithIndex rndbatch(db->DefaultColumnFamily()->GetComparator(),
274 0, true, 0);
275 for (size_t k = 0; k < 10; k++) { // 10 key per batch
276 size_t ki = static_cast<size_t>(rnd.Uniform(TOTAL_KEYS));
277 Slice key = Slice(keys[ki]);
278 std::string tmp = rnd.RandomString(16);
279 Slice value = Slice(tmp);
280 ASSERT_OK(rndbatch.Put(key, value));
281 }
282 SubBatchCounter batch_counter(comparators);
283 ASSERT_OK(rndbatch.GetWriteBatch()->Iterate(&batch_counter));
284 ASSERT_EQ(rndbatch.SubBatchCnt(), batch_counter.BatchCount());
285 }
286 }
287
288 delete cf_handle;
289 delete db;
290}

292TEST(CommitEntry64b, BasicTest) {
293 const size_t INDEX_BITS = static_cast<size_t>(21);
294 const size_t INDEX_SIZE = static_cast<size_t>(1ull << INDEX_BITS);
295 const CommitEntry64bFormat FORMAT(static_cast<size_t>(INDEX_BITS));
296
297 // zero-initialized CommitEntry64b should indicate an empty entry
298 CommitEntry64b empty_entry64b;
299 uint64_t empty_index = 11ul;
300 CommitEntry empty_entry;
301 bool ok = empty_entry64b.Parse(empty_index, &empty_entry, FORMAT);
302 ASSERT_FALSE(ok);
303
304 // the zero entry is reserved for un-initialized entries
305 const size_t MAX_COMMIT = (1 << FORMAT.COMMIT_BITS) - 1 - 1;
306 // Samples over the numbers that are covered by that many index bits
307 std::array<uint64_t, 4> is = {{0, 1, INDEX_SIZE / 2 + 1, INDEX_SIZE - 1}};
308 // Samples over the numbers that are covered by that many commit bits
309 std::array<uint64_t, 4> ds = {{0, 1, MAX_COMMIT / 2 + 1, MAX_COMMIT}};
310 // Iterate over prepare numbers that have i) cover all bits of a sequence
311 // number, and ii) include some bits that fall into the range of index or
312 // commit bits
313 for (uint64_t base = 1; base < kMaxSequenceNumber; base *= 2) {
314 for (uint64_t i : is) {
315 for (uint64_t d : ds) {
316 uint64_t p = base + i + d;
317 for (uint64_t c : {p, p + d / 2, p + d}) {
318 uint64_t index = p % INDEX_SIZE;
319 CommitEntry before(p, c), after;
320 CommitEntry64b entry64b(before, FORMAT);
321 ok = entry64b.Parse(index, &after, FORMAT);
322 ASSERT_TRUE(ok);
323 if (!(before == after)) {
324 printf("base %" PRIu64 " i %" PRIu64 " d %" PRIu64 " p %" PRIu64
325 " c %" PRIu64 " index %" PRIu64 "\n",
326 base, i, d, p, c, index);
327 }
328 ASSERT_EQ(before, after);
329 }
330 }
331 }
332 }

371 // If expect_update is set, check if it actually updated old_commit_map_. If
372 // it did not and yet suggested not to check the next snapshot, do the
373 // opposite to check if it was not a bad suggestion.
374 void MaybeUpdateOldCommitMapTestWithNext(uint64_t prepare, uint64_t commit,
375 uint64_t snapshot,
376 uint64_t next_snapshot,
377 bool expect_update) {
378 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
379 // reset old_commit_map_empty_ so that its value indicate whether
380 // old_commit_map_ was updated
381 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true;
382 bool check_next = wp_db->MaybeUpdateOldCommitMap(prepare, commit, snapshot,
383 snapshot < next_snapshot);
384 if (expect_update == wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_) {
385 printf("prepare: %" PRIu64 " commit: %" PRIu64 " snapshot: %" PRIu64
386 " next: %" PRIu64 "\n",
387 prepare, commit, snapshot, next_snapshot);
388 }
389 EXPECT_EQ(!expect_update, wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
390 if (!check_next && wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_) {
391 // do the opposite to make sure it was not a bad suggestion
392 const bool dont_care_bool = true;
393 wp_db->MaybeUpdateOldCommitMap(prepare, commit, next_snapshot,
394 dont_care_bool);
395 if (!wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_) {
396 printf("prepare: %" PRIu64 " commit: %" PRIu64 " snapshot: %" PRIu64
397 " next: %" PRIu64 "\n",
398 prepare, commit, snapshot, next_snapshot);
399 }
400 EXPECT_TRUE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
401 }
402 }

404 // Test that a CheckAgainstSnapshots thread reading old_snapshots will not
405 // miss a snapshot because of a concurrent update by UpdateSnapshots that is
406 // writing new_snapshots. Both threads are broken at two points. The sync
407 // points to enforce them are specified by a1, a2, b1, and b2. CommitEntry
408 // entry is expected to be vital for one of the snapshots that is common
409 // between the old and new list of snapshots.
410 void SnapshotConcurrentAccessTestInternal(
411 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db,
412 const std::vector<SequenceNumber>& old_snapshots,
413 const std::vector<SequenceNumber>& new_snapshots, CommitEntry& entry,
414 SequenceNumber& version, size_t a1, size_t a2, size_t b1, size_t b2) {
415 // First reset the snapshot list
416 const std::vector<SequenceNumber> empty_snapshots;
417 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true;
418 wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(empty_snapshots, ++version);
419 // Then initialize it with the old_snapshots
420 wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(old_snapshots, ++version);
421
422 // Starting from the first thread, cut each thread at two points
423 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency({
424 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(a1),
425 "WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:s:start"},
426 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(b1),
427 "WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(a1)},
428 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(a2),
429 "WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(b1)},
430 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(b2),
431 "WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(a2)},
432 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:p:end",
433 "WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(b2)},
434 });
435 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
436 {
437 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
438 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread t1(
439 [&]() { wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(new_snapshots, version); });
440 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(entry);
441 t1.join();
442 ASSERT_FALSE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
443 }
444 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
445
446 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true;
447 wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(empty_snapshots, ++version);
448 wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(old_snapshots, ++version);
449 // Starting from the second thread, cut each thread at two points
450 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency({
451 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(a1),
452 "WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:s:start"},
453 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(b1),
454 "WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(a1)},
455 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(a2),
456 "WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(b1)},
457 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:p:" + std::to_string(b2),
458 "WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(a2)},
459 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::UpdateSnapshots:p:end",
460 "WritePreparedTxnDB::CheckAgainstSnapshots:s:" + std::to_string(b2)},
461 });
462 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
463 {
464 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
465 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread t1(
466 [&]() { wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(new_snapshots, version); });
467 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(entry);
468 t1.join();
469 ASSERT_FALSE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
470 }
471 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
472 }

474 // Verify value of keys.
475 void VerifyKeys(const std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string>& data,
476 const Snapshot* snapshot = nullptr) {
477 std::string value;
478 ReadOptions read_options;
479 read_options.snapshot = snapshot;
480 for (auto& kv : data) {
481 auto s = db->Get(read_options, kv.first, &value);
482 ASSERT_TRUE(s.ok() || s.IsNotFound());
483 if (s.ok()) {
484 if (kv.second != value) {
485 printf("key = %s\n", kv.first.c_str());
486 }
487 ASSERT_EQ(kv.second, value);
488 } else {
489 ASSERT_EQ(kv.second, "NOT_FOUND");
490 }
491
492 // Try with MultiGet API too
493 std::vector<std::string> values;
494 auto s_vec = db->MultiGet(read_options, {db->DefaultColumnFamily()},
495 {kv.first}, &values);
496 ASSERT_EQ(1, values.size());
497 ASSERT_EQ(1, s_vec.size());
498 s = s_vec[0];
499 ASSERT_TRUE(s.ok() || s.IsNotFound());
500 if (s.ok()) {
501 ASSERT_TRUE(kv.second == values[0]);
502 } else {
503 ASSERT_EQ(kv.second, "NOT_FOUND");
504 }
505 }
506 }
507
508 // Verify all versions of keys.
509 void VerifyInternalKeys(const std::vector<KeyVersion>& expected_versions) {
510 std::vector<KeyVersion> versions;
511 const size_t kMaxKeys = 100000;
512 ASSERT_OK(GetAllKeyVersions(db, expected_versions.front().user_key,
513 expected_versions.back().user_key, kMaxKeys,
514 &versions));
515 ASSERT_EQ(expected_versions.size(), versions.size());
516 for (size_t i = 0; i < versions.size(); i++) {
517 ASSERT_EQ(expected_versions[i].user_key, versions[i].user_key);
518 ASSERT_EQ(expected_versions[i].sequence, versions[i].sequence);
519 ASSERT_EQ(expected_versions[i].type, versions[i].type);
520 if (versions[i].type != kTypeDeletion &&
521 versions[i].type != kTypeSingleDeletion) {
522 ASSERT_EQ(expected_versions[i].value, versions[i].value);
523 }
524 // Range delete not supported.
525 ASSERT_NE(expected_versions[i].type, kTypeRangeDeletion);
526 }
527 }

584 WritePreparedTransaction, WritePreparedTransactionTest,
585 ::testing::Values(
586 std::make_tuple(false, false, WRITE_PREPARED, kOrderedWrite),
587 std::make_tuple(false, true, WRITE_PREPARED, kOrderedWrite),

699TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, CommitMap) {
700 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
701 ASSERT_NE(wp_db, nullptr);
702 ASSERT_NE(wp_db->db_impl_, nullptr);
703 size_t size = wp_db->COMMIT_CACHE_SIZE;
704 CommitEntry c = {5, 12}, e;
705 bool evicted = wp_db->AddCommitEntry(c.prep_seq % size, c, &e);
706 ASSERT_FALSE(evicted);
707
708 // Should be able to read the same value
709 CommitEntry64b dont_care;
710 bool found = wp_db->GetCommitEntry(c.prep_seq % size, &dont_care, &e);
711 ASSERT_TRUE(found);
712 ASSERT_EQ(c, e);
713 // Should be able to distinguish between overlapping entries
714 found = wp_db->GetCommitEntry((c.prep_seq + size) % size, &dont_care, &e);
715 ASSERT_TRUE(found);
716 ASSERT_NE(c.prep_seq + size, e.prep_seq);
717 // Should be able to detect non-existent entry
718 found = wp_db->GetCommitEntry((c.prep_seq + 1) % size, &dont_care, &e);
719 ASSERT_FALSE(found);
720
721 // Reject an invalid exchange
722 CommitEntry e2 = {c.prep_seq + size, c.commit_seq + size};
723 CommitEntry64b e2_64b(e2, wp_db->FORMAT);
724 bool exchanged = wp_db->ExchangeCommitEntry(e2.prep_seq % size, e2_64b, e);
725 ASSERT_FALSE(exchanged);
726 // check whether it did actually reject that
727 found = wp_db->GetCommitEntry(e2.prep_seq % size, &dont_care, &e);
728 ASSERT_TRUE(found);
729 ASSERT_EQ(c, e);
730
731 // Accept a valid exchange
732 CommitEntry64b c_64b(c, wp_db->FORMAT);
733 CommitEntry e3 = {c.prep_seq + size, c.commit_seq + size + 1};
734 exchanged = wp_db->ExchangeCommitEntry(c.prep_seq % size, c_64b, e3);
735 ASSERT_TRUE(exchanged);
736 // check whether it did actually accepted that
737 found = wp_db->GetCommitEntry(c.prep_seq % size, &dont_care, &e);
738 ASSERT_TRUE(found);
739 ASSERT_EQ(e3, e);
740
741 // Rewrite an entry
742 CommitEntry e4 = {e3.prep_seq + size, e3.commit_seq + size + 1};
743 evicted = wp_db->AddCommitEntry(e4.prep_seq % size, e4, &e);
744 ASSERT_TRUE(evicted);
745 ASSERT_EQ(e3, e);
746 found = wp_db->GetCommitEntry(e4.prep_seq % size, &dont_care, &e);
747 ASSERT_TRUE(found);
748 ASSERT_EQ(e4, e);
749}

788// Trigger the condition where some old memtables are skipped when doing
789// TransactionUtil::CheckKey(), and make sure the result is still correct.
790TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, CheckKeySkipOldMemtable) {
791 const int kAttemptHistoryMemtable = 0;
792 const int kAttemptImmMemTable = 1;
793 for (int attempt = kAttemptHistoryMemtable; attempt <= kAttemptImmMemTable;
794 attempt++) {
795 options.max_write_buffer_number_to_maintain = 3;
796 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
797
798 WriteOptions write_options;
799 ReadOptions read_options;
800 TransactionOptions txn_options;
801 txn_options.set_snapshot = true;
802 string value;
803
804 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(write_options, Slice("foo"), Slice("bar")));
805 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(write_options, Slice("foo2"), Slice("bar")));
806
807 Transaction* txn = db->BeginTransaction(write_options, txn_options);
808 ASSERT_TRUE(txn != nullptr);
809 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("txn"));
810
811 Transaction* txn2 = db->BeginTransaction(write_options, txn_options);
812 ASSERT_TRUE(txn2 != nullptr);
813 ASSERT_OK(txn2->SetName("txn2"));
814
815 // This transaction is created to cause potential conflict.
816 Transaction* txn_x = db->BeginTransaction(write_options);
817 ASSERT_OK(txn_x->SetName("txn_x"));
818 ASSERT_OK(txn_x->Put(Slice("foo"), Slice("bar3")));
819 ASSERT_OK(txn_x->Prepare());
820
821 // Create snapshots after the prepare, but there should still
822 // be a conflict when trying to read "foo".
823
824 if (attempt == kAttemptImmMemTable) {
825 // For the second attempt, hold flush from beginning. The memtable
826 // will be switched to immutable after calling TEST_SwitchMemtable()
827 // while CheckKey() is called.
828 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency(
829 {{"WritePreparedTransactionTest.CheckKeySkipOldMemtable",
830 "FlushJob::Start"}});
831 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
832 }
833
834 // force a memtable flush. The memtable should still be kept
835 FlushOptions flush_ops;
836 if (attempt == kAttemptHistoryMemtable) {
837 ASSERT_OK(db->Flush(flush_ops));
838 } else {
839 ASSERT_EQ(attempt, kAttemptImmMemTable);
840 DBImpl* db_impl = static_cast<DBImpl*>(db->GetRootDB());
841 ASSERT_OK(db_impl->TEST_SwitchMemtable());
842 }
843 uint64_t num_imm_mems;
844 ASSERT_TRUE(db->GetIntProperty(DB::Properties::kNumImmutableMemTable,
845 &num_imm_mems));
846 if (attempt == kAttemptHistoryMemtable) {
847 ASSERT_EQ(0, num_imm_mems);
848 } else {
849 ASSERT_EQ(attempt, kAttemptImmMemTable);
850 ASSERT_EQ(1, num_imm_mems);
851 }
852
853 // Put something in active memtable
854 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(write_options, Slice("foo3"), Slice("bar")));
855
856 // Create txn3 after flushing, but this transaction also needs to
857 // check all memtables because of they contains uncommitted data.
858 Transaction* txn3 = db->BeginTransaction(write_options, txn_options);
859 ASSERT_TRUE(txn3 != nullptr);
860 ASSERT_OK(txn3->SetName("txn3"));
861
862 // Commit the pending write
863 ASSERT_OK(txn_x->Commit());
864
865 // Commit txn, txn2 and tx3. txn and tx3 will conflict but txn2 will
866 // pass. In all cases, both memtables are queried.
867 SetPerfLevel(PerfLevel::kEnableCount);
868 get_perf_context()->Reset();
869 ASSERT_TRUE(txn3->GetForUpdate(read_options, "foo", &value).IsBusy());
870 // We should have checked two memtables, active and either immutable
871 // or history memtable, depending on the test case.
872 ASSERT_EQ(2, get_perf_context()->get_from_memtable_count);
873
874 get_perf_context()->Reset();
875 ASSERT_TRUE(txn->GetForUpdate(read_options, "foo", &value).IsBusy());
876 // We should have checked two memtables, active and either immutable
877 // or history memtable, depending on the test case.
878 ASSERT_EQ(2, get_perf_context()->get_from_memtable_count);
879
880 get_perf_context()->Reset();
881 ASSERT_OK(txn2->GetForUpdate(read_options, "foo2", &value));
882 ASSERT_EQ(value, "bar");
883 // We should have checked two memtables, and since there is no
884 // conflict, another Get() will be made and fetch the data from
885 // DB. If it is in immutable memtable, two extra memtable reads
886 // will be issued. If it is not (in history), only one will
887 // be made, which is to the active memtable.
888 if (attempt == kAttemptHistoryMemtable) {
889 ASSERT_EQ(3, get_perf_context()->get_from_memtable_count);
890 } else {
891 ASSERT_EQ(attempt, kAttemptImmMemTable);
892 ASSERT_EQ(4, get_perf_context()->get_from_memtable_count);
893 }
894
895 Transaction* txn4 = db->BeginTransaction(write_options, txn_options);
896 ASSERT_TRUE(txn4 != nullptr);
897 ASSERT_OK(txn4->SetName("txn4"));
898 get_perf_context()->Reset();
899 ASSERT_OK(txn4->GetForUpdate(read_options, "foo", &value));
900 if (attempt == kAttemptHistoryMemtable) {
901 // Active memtable will be checked in snapshot validation and when
902 // getting the value.
903 ASSERT_EQ(2, get_perf_context()->get_from_memtable_count);
904 } else {
905 // Only active memtable will be checked in snapshot validation but
906 // both of active and immutable snapshot will be queried when
907 // getting the value.
908 ASSERT_EQ(attempt, kAttemptImmMemTable);
909 ASSERT_EQ(3, get_perf_context()->get_from_memtable_count);
910 }
911
912 ASSERT_OK(txn2->Commit());
913 ASSERT_OK(txn4->Commit());
914
915 TEST_SYNC_POINT("WritePreparedTransactionTest.CheckKeySkipOldMemtable");
916 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
917
918 SetPerfLevel(PerfLevel::kDisable);
919
920 delete txn;
921 delete txn2;
922 delete txn3;
923 delete txn4;
924 delete txn_x;
925 }
926}

928// Reproduce the bug with two snapshots with the same seuqence number and test
929// that the release of the first snapshot will not affect the reads by the other
930// snapshot
931TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, DoubleSnapshot) {
932 TransactionOptions txn_options;
933 Status s;
934
935 // Insert initial value
936 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "key", "value1"));
937
938 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
939 Transaction* txn =
940 wp_db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions(), txn_options, nullptr);
941 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("txn"));
942 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put("key", "value2"));
943 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
944 // Three snapshots with the same seq number
945 const Snapshot* snapshot0 = wp_db->GetSnapshot();
946 const Snapshot* snapshot1 = wp_db->GetSnapshot();
947 const Snapshot* snapshot2 = wp_db->GetSnapshot();
948 ASSERT_OK(txn->Commit());
949 SequenceNumber cache_size = wp_db->COMMIT_CACHE_SIZE;
950 SequenceNumber overlap_seq = txn->GetId() + cache_size;
951 delete txn;
952
953 // 4th snapshot with a larger seq
954 const Snapshot* snapshot3 = wp_db->GetSnapshot();
955 // Cause an eviction to advance max evicted seq number
956 // This also fetches the 4 snapshots from db since their seq is lower than the
957 // new max
958 wp_db->AddCommitted(overlap_seq, overlap_seq);
959
960 ReadOptions ropt;
961 // It should see the value before commit
962 ropt.snapshot = snapshot2;
963 PinnableSlice pinnable_val;
964 s = wp_db->Get(ropt, wp_db->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key", &pinnable_val);
965 ASSERT_OK(s);
966 ASSERT_TRUE(pinnable_val == "value1");
967 pinnable_val.Reset();
968
969 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot1);
970
971 // It should still see the value before commit
972 s = wp_db->Get(ropt, wp_db->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key", &pinnable_val);
973 ASSERT_OK(s);
974 ASSERT_TRUE(pinnable_val == "value1");
975 pinnable_val.Reset();
976
977 // Cause an eviction to advance max evicted seq number and trigger updating
978 // the snapshot list
979 overlap_seq += cache_size;
980 wp_db->AddCommitted(overlap_seq, overlap_seq);
981
982 // It should still see the value before commit
983 s = wp_db->Get(ropt, wp_db->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key", &pinnable_val);
984 ASSERT_OK(s);
985 ASSERT_TRUE(pinnable_val == "value1");
986 pinnable_val.Reset();
987
988 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot0);
989 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot2);
990 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot3);
991}

993size_t UniqueCnt(std::vector<SequenceNumber> vec) {
994 std::set<SequenceNumber> aset;
995 for (auto i : vec) {
996 aset.insert(i);
997 }
998 return aset.size();
999}
1000// Test that the entries in old_commit_map_ get garbage collected properly
1001TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, OldCommitMapGC) {
1002 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 0;
1003 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 0;
1004 DBImpl* mock_db = new DBImpl(options, dbname);
1005 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
1006 std::unique_ptr<WritePreparedTxnDBMock> wp_db(
1007 new WritePreparedTxnDBMock(mock_db, txn_db_options));
1008
1009 SequenceNumber seq = 0;
1010 // Take the first snapshot that overlaps with two txn
1011 auto prep_seq = ++seq;
1012 wp_db->AddPrepared(prep_seq);
1013 auto prep_seq2 = ++seq;
1014 wp_db->AddPrepared(prep_seq2);
1015 auto snap_seq1 = seq;
1016 wp_db->TakeSnapshot(snap_seq1);
1017 auto commit_seq = ++seq;
1018 wp_db->AddCommitted(prep_seq, commit_seq);
1019 wp_db->RemovePrepared(prep_seq);
1020 auto commit_seq2 = ++seq;
1021 wp_db->AddCommitted(prep_seq2, commit_seq2);
1022 wp_db->RemovePrepared(prep_seq2);
1023 // Take the 2nd and 3rd snapshot that overlap with the same txn
1024 prep_seq = ++seq;
1025 wp_db->AddPrepared(prep_seq);
1026 auto snap_seq2 = seq;
1027 wp_db->TakeSnapshot(snap_seq2);
1028 seq++;
1029 auto snap_seq3 = seq;
1030 wp_db->TakeSnapshot(snap_seq3);
1031 seq++;
1032 commit_seq = ++seq;
1033 wp_db->AddCommitted(prep_seq, commit_seq);
1034 wp_db->RemovePrepared(prep_seq);
1035 // Make sure max_evicted_seq_ will be larger than 2nd snapshot by evicting the
1036 // only item in the commit_cache_ via another commit.
1037 prep_seq = ++seq;
1038 wp_db->AddPrepared(prep_seq);
1039 commit_seq = ++seq;
1040 wp_db->AddCommitted(prep_seq, commit_seq);
1041 wp_db->RemovePrepared(prep_seq);
1042
1043 // Verify that the evicted commit entries for all snapshots are in the
1044 // old_commit_map_
1045 {
1046 ASSERT_FALSE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_.load());
1047 ReadLock rl(&wp_db->old_commit_map_mutex_);
1048 ASSERT_EQ(3, wp_db->old_commit_map_.size());
1049 ASSERT_EQ(2, UniqueCnt(wp_db->old_commit_map_[snap_seq1]));
1050 ASSERT_EQ(1, UniqueCnt(wp_db->old_commit_map_[snap_seq2]));
1051 ASSERT_EQ(1, UniqueCnt(wp_db->old_commit_map_[snap_seq3]));
1052 }
1053
1054 // Verify that the 2nd snapshot is cleaned up after the release
1055 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshotInternal(snap_seq2);
1056 {

1061 ASSERT_EQ(1, UniqueCnt(wp_db->old_commit_map_[snap_seq3]));

1065 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshotInternal(snap_seq1);

1068 ReadLock rl(&wp_db->old_commit_map_mutex_);
1069 ASSERT_EQ(1, wp_db->old_commit_map_.size());
1070 ASSERT_EQ(1, UniqueCnt(wp_db->old_commit_map_[snap_seq3]));

1074 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshotInternal(snap_seq3);

1076 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_.load());
1077 ReadLock rl(&wp_db->old_commit_map_mutex_);
1078 ASSERT_EQ(0, wp_db->old_commit_map_.size());

1082TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, CheckAgainstSnapshots) {
1083 std::vector<SequenceNumber> snapshots = {100l, 200l, 300l, 400l, 500l,
1084 600l, 700l, 800l, 900l};
1085 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 2;
1086 const uint64_t cache_size = 1ul << snapshot_cache_bits;
1087 // Safety check to express the intended size in the test. Can be adjusted if
1088 // the snapshots lists changed.
1089 ASSERT_EQ((1ul << snapshot_cache_bits) * 2 + 1, snapshots.size());
1090 DBImpl* mock_db = new DBImpl(options, dbname);
1091 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits);
1092 std::unique_ptr<WritePreparedTxnDBMock> wp_db(
1093 new WritePreparedTxnDBMock(mock_db, txn_db_options));
1094 SequenceNumber version = 1000l;
1095 ASSERT_EQ(0, wp_db->snapshots_total_);
1096 wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(snapshots, version);
1097 ASSERT_EQ(snapshots.size(), wp_db->snapshots_total_);
1098 // seq numbers are chosen so that we have two of them between each two
1099 // snapshots. If the diff of two consecutive seq is more than 5, there is a
1100 // snapshot between them.
1101 std::vector<SequenceNumber> seqs = {50l, 55l, 150l, 155l, 250l, 255l, 350l,
1102 355l, 450l, 455l, 550l, 555l, 650l, 655l,
1103 750l, 755l, 850l, 855l, 950l, 955l};
1104 ASSERT_GT(seqs.size(), 1);
1105 for (size_t i = 0; i + 1 < seqs.size(); i++) {
1106 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true; // reset
1107 CommitEntry commit_entry = {seqs[i], seqs[i + 1]};
1108 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(commit_entry);
1109 // Expect update if there is snapshot in between the prepare and commit
1110 bool expect_update = commit_entry.commit_seq - commit_entry.prep_seq > 5 &&
1111 commit_entry.commit_seq >= snapshots.front() &&
1112 commit_entry.prep_seq <= snapshots.back();
1113 ASSERT_EQ(expect_update, !wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_);
1114 }
1115
1116 // Test that search will include multiple snapshot from snapshot cache
1117 {
1118 // exclude first and last item in the cache
1119 CommitEntry commit_entry = {snapshots.front() + 1,
1120 snapshots[cache_size - 1] - 1};
1121 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true; // reset
1122 wp_db->old_commit_map_.clear();
1123 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(commit_entry);
1124 ASSERT_EQ(wp_db->old_commit_map_.size(), cache_size - 2);
1125 }
1126
1127 // Test that search will include multiple snapshot from old snapshots
1128 {
1129 // include two in the middle
1130 CommitEntry commit_entry = {snapshots[cache_size] + 1,
1131 snapshots[cache_size + 2] + 1};
1132 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true; // reset
1133 wp_db->old_commit_map_.clear();
1134 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(commit_entry);
1135 ASSERT_EQ(wp_db->old_commit_map_.size(), 2);
1136 }
1137
1138 // Test that search will include both snapshot cache and old snapshots
1139 // Case 1: includes all in snapshot cache
1140 {
1141 CommitEntry commit_entry = {snapshots.front() - 1, snapshots.back() + 1};
1142 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true; // reset
1143 wp_db->old_commit_map_.clear();
1144 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(commit_entry);
1145 ASSERT_EQ(wp_db->old_commit_map_.size(), snapshots.size());
1146 }
1147
1148 // Case 2: includes all snapshot caches except the smallest
1149 {
1150 CommitEntry commit_entry = {snapshots.front() + 1, snapshots.back() + 1};
1151 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true; // reset
1152 wp_db->old_commit_map_.clear();
1153 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(commit_entry);
1154 ASSERT_EQ(wp_db->old_commit_map_.size(), snapshots.size() - 1);
1155 }
1156
1157 // Case 3: includes only the largest of snapshot cache
1158 {
1159 CommitEntry commit_entry = {snapshots[cache_size - 1] - 1,
1160 snapshots.back() + 1};
1161 wp_db->old_commit_map_empty_ = true; // reset
1162 wp_db->old_commit_map_.clear();
1163 wp_db->CheckAgainstSnapshots(commit_entry);
1164 ASSERT_EQ(wp_db->old_commit_map_.size(), snapshots.size() - cache_size + 1);
1165 }
1166}

1168#if !defined(ROCKSDB_VALGRIND_RUN) || defined(ROCKSDB_FULL_VALGRIND_RUN)
1169// Test that CheckAgainstSnapshots will not miss a live snapshot if it is run in
1170// parallel with UpdateSnapshots.
1171TEST_P(SnapshotConcurrentAccessTest, SnapshotConcurrentAccess) {
1172 // We have a sync point in the method under test after checking each snapshot.
1173 // If you increase the max number of snapshots in this test, more sync points
1174 // in the methods must also be added.
1175 const std::vector<SequenceNumber> snapshots = {10l, 20l, 30l, 40l, 50l,
1176 60l, 70l, 80l, 90l, 100l};
1177 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 2;
1178 // Safety check to express the intended size in the test. Can be adjusted if
1179 // the snapshots lists changed.
1180 ASSERT_EQ((1ul << snapshot_cache_bits) * 2 + 2, snapshots.size());
1181 SequenceNumber version = 1000l;
1182 // Choose the cache size so that the new snapshot list could replace all the
1183 // existing items in the cache and also have some overflow.
1184 DBImpl* mock_db = new DBImpl(options, dbname);
1185 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits);
1186 std::unique_ptr<WritePreparedTxnDBMock> wp_db(
1187 new WritePreparedTxnDBMock(mock_db, txn_db_options));
1188 const size_t extra = 2;
1189 size_t loop_id = 0;
1190 // Add up to extra items that do not fit into the cache
1191 for (size_t old_size = 1; old_size <= wp_db->SNAPSHOT_CACHE_SIZE + extra;
1192 old_size++) {
1193 const std::vector<SequenceNumber> old_snapshots(
1194 snapshots.begin(), snapshots.begin() + old_size);
1195
1196 // Each member of old snapshot might or might not appear in the new list. We
1197 // create a common_snapshots for each combination.
1198 size_t new_comb_cnt = size_t(1) << old_size;
1199 for (size_t new_comb = 0; new_comb < new_comb_cnt; new_comb++, loop_id++) {
1200 if (loop_id % split_cnt_ != split_id_) {
1201 continue;
1202 }
1203 printf("."); // To signal progress
1204 fflush(stdout);
1205 std::vector<SequenceNumber> common_snapshots;
1206 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_snapshots.size(); i++) {
1207 if (IsInCombination(i, new_comb)) {
1208 common_snapshots.push_back(old_snapshots[i]);
1209 }
1210 }
1211 // And add some new snapshots to the common list
1212 for (size_t added_snapshots = 0;
1213 added_snapshots <= snapshots.size() - old_snapshots.size();
1214 added_snapshots++) {
1215 std::vector<SequenceNumber> new_snapshots = common_snapshots;
1216 for (size_t i = 0; i < added_snapshots; i++) {
1217 new_snapshots.push_back(snapshots[old_snapshots.size() + i]);
1218 }
1219 for (auto it = common_snapshots.begin(); it != common_snapshots.end();
1220 ++it) {
1221 auto snapshot = *it;
1222 // Create a commit entry that is around the snapshot and thus should
1223 // be not be discarded
1224 CommitEntry entry = {static_cast<uint64_t>(snapshot - 1),
1225 snapshot + 1};
1226 // The critical part is when iterating the snapshot cache. Afterwards,
1227 // we are operating under the lock
1228 size_t a_range =
1229 std::min(old_snapshots.size(), wp_db->SNAPSHOT_CACHE_SIZE) + 1;
1230 size_t b_range =
1231 std::min(new_snapshots.size(), wp_db->SNAPSHOT_CACHE_SIZE) + 1;
1232 // Break each thread at two points
1233 for (size_t a1 = 1; a1 <= a_range; a1++) {
1234 for (size_t a2 = a1 + 1; a2 <= a_range; a2++) {
1235 for (size_t b1 = 1; b1 <= b_range; b1++) {
1236 for (size_t b2 = b1 + 1; b2 <= b_range; b2++) {
1237 SnapshotConcurrentAccessTestInternal(
1238 wp_db.get(), old_snapshots, new_snapshots, entry, version,
1239 a1, a2, b1, b2);
1240 }
1241 }
1242 }
1243 }
1244 }
1245 }
1246 }
1247 }
1248 printf("\n");
1249}

1252// This test clarifies the contract of AdvanceMaxEvictedSeq method
1253TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, AdvanceMaxEvictedSeqBasic) {
1254 DBImpl* mock_db = new DBImpl(options, dbname);
1255 std::unique_ptr<WritePreparedTxnDBMock> wp_db(
1256 new WritePreparedTxnDBMock(mock_db, txn_db_options));
1257
1258 // 1. Set the initial values for max, prepared, and snapshots
1259 SequenceNumber zero_max = 0l;
1260 // Set the initial list of prepared txns
1261 const std::vector<SequenceNumber> initial_prepared = {10, 30, 50, 100,
1262 150, 200, 250};
1263 for (auto p : initial_prepared) {
1264 wp_db->AddPrepared(p);
1265 }
1266 // This updates the max value and also set old prepared
1267 SequenceNumber init_max = 100;
1268 wp_db->AdvanceMaxEvictedSeq(zero_max, init_max);
1269 const std::vector<SequenceNumber> initial_snapshots = {20, 40};
1270 wp_db->SetDBSnapshots(initial_snapshots);
1271 // This will update the internal cache of snapshots from the DB
1272 wp_db->UpdateSnapshots(initial_snapshots, init_max);
1273
1274 // 2. Invoke AdvanceMaxEvictedSeq
1275 const std::vector<SequenceNumber> latest_snapshots = {20, 110, 220, 300};
1276 wp_db->SetDBSnapshots(latest_snapshots);
1277 SequenceNumber new_max = 200;
1278 wp_db->AdvanceMaxEvictedSeq(init_max, new_max);
1279
1280 // 3. Verify that the state matches with AdvanceMaxEvictedSeq contract
1281 // a. max should be updated to new_max
1282 ASSERT_EQ(wp_db->max_evicted_seq_, new_max);
1283 // b. delayed prepared should contain every txn <= max and prepared should
1284 // only contain txns > max
1285 auto it = initial_prepared.begin();
1286 for (; it != initial_prepared.end() && *it <= new_max; ++it) {
1287 ASSERT_EQ(1, wp_db->delayed_prepared_.erase(*it));
1288 }
1289 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->delayed_prepared_.empty());
1290 for (; it != initial_prepared.end() && !wp_db->prepared_txns_.empty();
1291 ++it, wp_db->prepared_txns_.pop()) {
1292 ASSERT_EQ(*it, wp_db->prepared_txns_.top());
1293 }
1294 ASSERT_TRUE(it == initial_prepared.end());
1295 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->prepared_txns_.empty());
1296 // c. snapshots should contain everything below new_max
1297 auto sit = latest_snapshots.begin();
1298 for (size_t i = 0; sit != latest_snapshots.end() && *sit <= new_max &&
1299 i < wp_db->snapshots_total_;
1300 sit++, i++) {
1301 ASSERT_TRUE(i < wp_db->snapshots_total_);
1302 // This test is in small scale and the list of snapshots are assumed to be
1303 // within the cache size limit. This is just a safety check to double check
1304 // that assumption.
1305 ASSERT_TRUE(i < wp_db->SNAPSHOT_CACHE_SIZE);
1306 ASSERT_EQ(*sit, wp_db->snapshot_cache_[i]);
1307 }
1308}

1310// A new snapshot should always be always larger than max_evicted_seq_
1311// Otherwise the snapshot does not go through AdvanceMaxEvictedSeq
1312TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, NewSnapshotLargerThanMax) {
1313 WriteOptions woptions;
1314 TransactionOptions txn_options;
1315 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
1316 Transaction* txn0 = db->BeginTransaction(woptions, txn_options);
1317 ASSERT_OK(txn0->Put(Slice("key"), Slice("value")));
1318 ASSERT_OK(txn0->Commit());
1319 const SequenceNumber seq = txn0->GetId(); // is also prepare seq
1320 delete txn0;
1321 std::vector<Transaction*> txns;
1322 // Inc seq without committing anything
1323 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
1324 Transaction* txn = db->BeginTransaction(woptions, txn_options);
1325 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("xid" + std::to_string(i)));
1326 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put(Slice("key" + std::to_string(i)), Slice("value")));
1327 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
1328 txns.push_back(txn);
1329 }
1330
1331 // The new commit is seq + 10
1332 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(woptions, "key", "value"));
1333 auto snap = wp_db->GetSnapshot();
1334 const SequenceNumber last_seq = snap->GetSequenceNumber();
1335 wp_db->ReleaseSnapshot(snap);
1336 ASSERT_LT(seq, last_seq);
1337 // Otherwise our test is not effective
1338 ASSERT_LT(last_seq - seq, wp_db->INC_STEP_FOR_MAX_EVICTED);
1339
1340 // Evict seq out of commit cache
1341 const SequenceNumber overwrite_seq = seq + wp_db->COMMIT_CACHE_SIZE;
1342 // Check that the next write could make max go beyond last
1343 auto last_max = wp_db->max_evicted_seq_.load();
1344 wp_db->AddCommitted(overwrite_seq, overwrite_seq);
1345 // Check that eviction has advanced the max
1346 ASSERT_LT(last_max, wp_db->max_evicted_seq_.load());
1347 // Check that the new max has not advanced the last seq
1348 ASSERT_LT(wp_db->max_evicted_seq_.load(), last_seq);
1349 for (auto txn : txns) {
1350 ASSERT_OK(txn->Rollback());
1351 delete txn;
1352 }
1353}

1355// A new snapshot should always be always larger than max_evicted_seq_
1356// In very rare cases max could be below last published seq. Test that
1357// taking snapshot will wait for max to catch up.
1358TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, MaxCatchupWithNewSnapshot) {
1359 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 7; // same as default
1360 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 0; // only 1 entry => frequent eviction
1361 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
1362 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
1363 WriteOptions woptions;
1364 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
1365
1366 const int writes = 50;
1367 const int batch_cnt = 4;
1368 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread t1([&]() {
1369 for (int i = 0; i < writes; i++) {
1370 WriteBatch batch;
1371 // For duplicate keys cause 4 commit entries, each evicting an entry that
1372 // is not published yet, thus causing max evicted seq go higher than last
1373 // published.
1374 for (int b = 0; b < batch_cnt; b++) {
1375 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("foo", "foo"));
1376 }
1377 ASSERT_OK(db->Write(woptions, &batch));
1378 }
1379 });
1380
1381 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread t2([&]() {
1382 while (wp_db->max_evicted_seq_ == 0) { // wait for insert thread
1383 std::this_thread::yield();
1384 }
1385 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
1386 SequenceNumber max_lower_bound = wp_db->max_evicted_seq_;
1387 auto snap = db->GetSnapshot();
1388 if (snap->GetSequenceNumber() != 0) {
1389 // Value of max_evicted_seq_ when snapshot was taken in unknown. We thus
1390 // compare with the lower bound instead as an approximation.
1391 ASSERT_LT(max_lower_bound, snap->GetSequenceNumber());
1392 } // seq 0 is ok to be less than max since nothing is visible to it
1393 db->ReleaseSnapshot(snap);
1394 }
1395 });
1396
1397 t1.join();
1398 t2.join();
1399
1400 // Make sure that the test has worked and seq number has advanced as we
1401 // thought
1402 auto snap = db->GetSnapshot();
1403 ASSERT_GT(snap->GetSequenceNumber(), batch_cnt * writes - 1);
1404 db->ReleaseSnapshot(snap);
1405}

1580// delayed_prepared_, when is run concurrently with advancing max_evicted_seq,
1581// which moves prepared txns from prepared_txns_ to delayed_prepared_.
1582TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, SmallestUnCommittedSeq) {
1583 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 7; // same as default
1584 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 1; // disable commit cache
1585 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
1586 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
1587 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
1588 ReadOptions ropt;
1589 PinnableSlice pinnable_val;
1590 WriteOptions write_options;
1591 TransactionOptions txn_options;
1592 std::vector<Transaction*> txns, committed_txns;
1593
1594 const int cnt = 100;
1595 for (int i = 0; i < cnt; i++) {
1596 Transaction* txn = db->BeginTransaction(write_options, txn_options);
1597 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("xid" + std::to_string(i)));
1598 auto key = "key1" + std::to_string(i);
1599 auto value = "value1" + std::to_string(i);
1600 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put(Slice(key), Slice(value)));
1601 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
1602 txns.push_back(txn);
1603 }
1604
1605 port::Mutex mutex;
1606 Random rnd(1103);
1607 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread commit_thread([&]() {
1608 for (int i = 0; i < cnt; i++) {
1609 uint32_t index = rnd.Uniform(cnt - i);
1610 Transaction* txn;
1611 {
1612 MutexLock l(&mutex);
1613 txn = txns[index];
1614 txns.erase(txns.begin() + index);
1615 }
1616 // Since commit cache is practically disabled, commit results in immediate
1617 // advance in max_evicted_seq_ and subsequently moving some prepared txns
1618 // to delayed_prepared_.
1619 ASSERT_OK(txn->Commit());
1620 committed_txns.push_back(txn);
1621 }
1622 });
1623 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread read_thread([&]() {
1624 while (true) {
1625 MutexLock l(&mutex);
1626 if (txns.empty()) {
1627 break;
1628 }
1629 auto min_uncommitted = wp_db->SmallestUnCommittedSeq();
1630 ASSERT_LE(min_uncommitted, (*txns.begin())->GetId());
1631 }
1632 });
1633
1634 commit_thread.join();
1635 read_thread.join();
1636 for (auto txn : committed_txns) {
1637 delete txn;
1638 }
1639}

1642TEST_P(SeqAdvanceConcurrentTest, SeqAdvanceConcurrent) {
1643 // Given the sequential run of txns, with this timeout we should never see a
1644 // deadlock nor a timeout unless we have a key conflict, which should be
1645 // almost infeasible.
1646 txn_db_options.transaction_lock_timeout = 1000;
1647 txn_db_options.default_lock_timeout = 1000;
1648 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
1649 FlushOptions fopt;
1650
1651 // Number of different txn types we use in this test
1652 const size_t type_cnt = 5;
1653 // The size of the first write group
1654 // TODO(myabandeh): This should be increase for pre-release tests
1655 const size_t first_group_size = 2;
1656 // Total number of txns we run in each test
1657 // TODO(myabandeh): This should be increase for pre-release tests
1658 const size_t txn_cnt = first_group_size + 1;
1659
1660 size_t base[txn_cnt + 1] = {
1661 1,
1662 };
1663 for (size_t bi = 1; bi <= txn_cnt; bi++) {
1664 base[bi] = base[bi - 1] * type_cnt;
1665 }
1666 const size_t max_n = static_cast<size_t>(std::pow(type_cnt, txn_cnt));
1667 printf("Number of cases being tested is %" ROCKSDB_PRIszt "\n", max_n);
1668 for (size_t n = 0; n < max_n; n++) {
1669 if (n > 0) {
1670 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
1671 }
1672
1673 if (n % split_cnt_ != split_id_) {
1674 continue;
1675 }
1676 if (n % 1000 == 0) {
1677 printf("Tested %" ROCKSDB_PRIszt " cases so far\n", n);
1678 }
1679 DBImpl* db_impl = static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db->GetRootDB());
1680 auto seq = db_impl->TEST_GetLastVisibleSequence();
1681 with_empty_commits = 0;
1682 exp_seq = seq;
1683 // This is increased before writing the batch for commit
1684 commit_writes = 0;
1685 // This is increased before txn starts linking if it expects to do a commit
1686 // eventually
1687 expected_commits = 0;
1688 std::vector<port::Thread> threads;
1689
1690 linked.store(0, std::memory_order_release);
1691 std::atomic<bool> batch_formed(false);
1692 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1693 "WriteThread::EnterAsBatchGroupLeader:End",
1694 [&](void* /*arg*/) { batch_formed = true; });
1695 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1696 "WriteThread::JoinBatchGroup:Wait", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
1697 size_t orig_linked = linked.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_acq_rel);
1698 if (orig_linked == 0) {
1699 // Wait until the others are linked too.
1700 while (linked.load(std::memory_order_acquire) < first_group_size) {
1701 }
1702 } else if (orig_linked == first_group_size) {
1703 // Make the 2nd batch of the rest of writes plus any followup
1704 // commits from the first batch
1705 while (linked.load(std::memory_order_acquire) <
1706 txn_cnt + commit_writes) {
1707 }
1708 }
1709 // Then we will have one or more batches consisting of follow-up
1710 // commits from the 2nd batch. There is a bit of non-determinism here
1711 // but it should be tolerable.
1712 });
1713
1714 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
1715 for (size_t bi = 0; bi < txn_cnt; bi++) {
1716 // get the bi-th digit in number system based on type_cnt
1717 size_t d = (n % base[bi + 1]) / base[bi];
1718 switch (d) {
1719 case 0:
1720 threads.emplace_back(&TransactionTestBase::TestTxn0, this, bi);
1721 break;
1722 case 1:
1723 threads.emplace_back(&TransactionTestBase::TestTxn1, this, bi);
1724 break;
1725 case 2:
1726 threads.emplace_back(&TransactionTestBase::TestTxn2, this, bi);
1727 break;
1728 case 3:
1729 threads.emplace_back(&TransactionTestBase::TestTxn3, this, bi);
1730 break;
1731 case 4:
1732 threads.emplace_back(&TransactionTestBase::TestTxn3, this, bi);
1733 break;
1734 default:
1735 FAIL();
1736 }
1737 // wait to be linked
1738 while (linked.load(std::memory_order_acquire) <= bi) {
1739 }
1740 // after a queue of size first_group_size
1741 if (bi + 1 == first_group_size) {
1742 while (!batch_formed) {
1743 }
1744 // to make it more deterministic, wait until the commits are linked
1745 while (linked.load(std::memory_order_acquire) <=
1746 bi + expected_commits) {
1747 }
1748 }
1749 }
1750 for (auto& t : threads) {
1751 t.join();
1752 }
1753 if (options.two_write_queues) {
1754 // In this case none of the above scheduling tricks to deterministically
1755 // form merged batches works because the writes go to separate queues.
1756 // This would result in different write groups in each run of the test. We
1757 // still keep the test since although non-deterministic and hard to debug,
1758 // it is still useful to have.
1759 // TODO(myabandeh): Add a deterministic unit test for two_write_queues
1760 }
1761
1762 // Check if memtable inserts advanced seq number as expected
1763 seq = db_impl->TEST_GetLastVisibleSequence();
1764 ASSERT_EQ(exp_seq, seq);
1765
1766 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
1767 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
1768
1769 // Check if recovery preserves the last sequence number
1770 ASSERT_OK(db_impl->FlushWAL(true));
1771 ASSERT_OK(ReOpenNoDelete());
1772 ASSERT_NE(db, nullptr);
1773 db_impl = static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db->GetRootDB());
1774 seq = db_impl->TEST_GetLastVisibleSequence();
1775 ASSERT_LE(exp_seq, seq + with_empty_commits);
1776
1777 // Check if flush preserves the last sequence number
1778 ASSERT_OK(db_impl->Flush(fopt));
1779 seq = db_impl->GetLatestSequenceNumber();
1780 ASSERT_LE(exp_seq, seq + with_empty_commits);
1781
1782 // Check if recovery after flush preserves the last sequence number
1783 ASSERT_OK(db_impl->FlushWAL(true));
1784 ASSERT_OK(ReOpenNoDelete());
1785 ASSERT_NE(db, nullptr);
1786 db_impl = static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db->GetRootDB());
1787 seq = db_impl->GetLatestSequenceNumber();
1788 ASSERT_LE(exp_seq, seq + with_empty_commits);
1789 }
1790}

2042 wp_db->IsInSnapshot(seq, snap_seq + 1, min_uncommitted, &released));

2056 ASSERT_TRUE(
2057 wp_db->IsInSnapshot(seq, snap_seq + 1, min_uncommitted, &released));

2059
2060 snap_seq = snap2->GetSequenceNumber();
2061
2062 released = false;
2063 // Unreleased snapshot lower than max
2064 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->IsInSnapshot(seq, snap_seq, min_uncommitted, &released));
2065 ASSERT_FALSE(released);

2070// Test WritePreparedTxnDB's IsInSnapshot against different ordering of
2071// snapshot, max_committed_seq_, prepared, and commit entries.
2072TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, IsInSnapshot) {
2073 WriteOptions wo;
2074 // Use small commit cache to trigger lots of eviction and fast advance of
2075 // max_evicted_seq_
2076 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 3;
2077 // Same for snapshot cache size
2078 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 2;
2079
2080 // Take some preliminary snapshots first. This is to stress the data structure
2081 // that holds the old snapshots as it will be designed to be efficient when
2082 // only a few snapshots are below the max_evicted_seq_.
2083 for (int max_snapshots = 1; max_snapshots < 20; max_snapshots++) {
2084 // Leave some gap between the preliminary snapshots and the final snapshot
2085 // that we check. This should test for also different overlapping scenarios
2086 // between the last snapshot and the commits.
2087 for (int max_gap = 1; max_gap < 10; max_gap++) {
2088 // Since we do not actually write to db, we mock the seq as it would be
2089 // increased by the db. The only exception is that we need db seq to
2090 // advance for our snapshots. for which we apply a dummy put each time we
2091 // increase our mock of seq.
2092 uint64_t seq = 0;
2093 // At each step we prepare a txn and then we commit it in the next txn.
2094 // This emulates the consecutive transactions that write to the same key
2095 uint64_t cur_txn = 0;
2096 // Number of snapshots taken so far
2097 int num_snapshots = 0;
2098 // Number of gaps applied so far
2099 int gap_cnt = 0;
2100 // The final snapshot that we will inspect
2101 uint64_t snapshot = 0;
2102 bool found_committed = false;
2103 // To stress the data structure that maintain prepared txns, at each cycle
2104 // we add a new prepare txn. These do not mean to be committed for
2105 // snapshot inspection.
2106 std::set<uint64_t> prepared;
2107 // We keep the list of txns committed before we take the last snapshot.
2108 // These should be the only seq numbers that will be found in the snapshot
2109 std::set<uint64_t> committed_before;
2110 // The set of commit seq numbers to be excluded from IsInSnapshot queries
2111 std::set<uint64_t> commit_seqs;
2112 DBImpl* mock_db = new DBImpl(options, dbname);
2113 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
2114 std::unique_ptr<WritePreparedTxnDBMock> wp_db(
2115 new WritePreparedTxnDBMock(mock_db, txn_db_options));
2116 // We continue until max advances a bit beyond the snapshot.
2117 while (!snapshot || wp_db->max_evicted_seq_ < snapshot + 100) {
2118 // do prepare for a transaction
2119 seq++;
2120 wp_db->AddPrepared(seq);
2121 prepared.insert(seq);
2122
2123 // If cur_txn is not started, do prepare for it.
2124 if (!cur_txn) {
2125 seq++;
2126 cur_txn = seq;
2127 wp_db->AddPrepared(cur_txn);
2128 } else { // else commit it
2129 seq++;
2130 wp_db->AddCommitted(cur_txn, seq);
2131 wp_db->RemovePrepared(cur_txn);
2132 commit_seqs.insert(seq);
2133 if (!snapshot) {
2134 committed_before.insert(cur_txn);
2135 }
2136 cur_txn = 0;
2137 }
2138
2139 if (num_snapshots < max_snapshots - 1) {
2140 // Take preliminary snapshots
2141 wp_db->TakeSnapshot(seq);
2142 num_snapshots++;
2143 } else if (gap_cnt < max_gap) {
2144 // Wait for some gap before taking the final snapshot
2145 gap_cnt++;
2146 } else if (!snapshot) {
2147 // Take the final snapshot if it is not already taken
2148 snapshot = seq;
2149 wp_db->TakeSnapshot(snapshot);
2150 num_snapshots++;
2151 }
2152
2153 // If the snapshot is taken, verify seq numbers visible to it. We redo
2154 // it at each cycle to test that the system is still sound when
2155 // max_evicted_seq_ advances.
2156 if (snapshot) {
2157 for (uint64_t s = 1;
2158 s <= seq && commit_seqs.find(s) == commit_seqs.end(); s++) {
2159 bool was_committed =
2160 (committed_before.find(s) != committed_before.end());
2161 bool is_in_snapshot = wp_db->IsInSnapshot(s, snapshot);
2162 if (was_committed != is_in_snapshot) {
2163 printf("max_snapshots %d max_gap %d seq %" PRIu64 " max %" PRIu64
2164 " snapshot %" PRIu64
2165 " gap_cnt %d num_snapshots %d s %" PRIu64 "\n",
2166 max_snapshots, max_gap, seq,
2167 wp_db->max_evicted_seq_.load(), snapshot, gap_cnt,
2168 num_snapshots, s);
2169 }
2170 ASSERT_EQ(was_committed, is_in_snapshot);
2171 found_committed = found_committed || is_in_snapshot;
2172 }
2173 }
2174 }
2175 // Safety check to make sure the test actually ran
2176 ASSERT_TRUE(found_committed);
2177 // As an extra check, check if prepared set will be properly empty after
2178 // they are committed.
2179 if (cur_txn) {
2180 wp_db->AddCommitted(cur_txn, seq);
2181 wp_db->RemovePrepared(cur_txn);
2182 }
2183 for (auto p : prepared) {
2184 wp_db->AddCommitted(p, seq);
2185 wp_db->RemovePrepared(p);
2186 }
2187 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->delayed_prepared_.empty());
2188 ASSERT_TRUE(wp_db->prepared_txns_.empty());
2189 }
2190 }
2191}

2581// Insert two values, v1 and v2, for a key. Between prepare and commit of v2
2582// take two snapshots, s1 and s2. Release s1 during compaction.

2585TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, ReleaseSnapshotDuringCompaction) {
2586 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 7; // same as default
2587 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 0; // minimum commit cache
2588 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
2589 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
2590 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());

2592 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "key1", "value1_1"));
2593 auto* transaction =
2594 db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions(), TransactionOptions(), nullptr);
2595 ASSERT_OK(transaction->SetName("txn"));
2596 ASSERT_OK(transaction->Put("key1", "value1_2"));
2597 ASSERT_OK(transaction->Prepare());
2598 auto snapshot1 = db->GetSnapshot();
2599 // Increment sequence number.
2600 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "key2", "value2"));
2601 auto snapshot2 = db->GetSnapshot();
2602 ASSERT_OK(transaction->Commit());
2603 delete transaction;
2604 VerifyKeys({{"key1", "value1_2"}});

2606 VerifyKeys({{"key1", "value1_1"}}, snapshot2);
2607 // Add a flush to avoid compaction to fallback to trivial move.
2608
2609 // The callback might be called twice, record the calling state to
2610 // prevent double calling.
2611 bool callback_finished = false;
2612 auto callback = [&](void*) {
2613 if (callback_finished) {
2614 return;
2615 }

2617 // CompactionIterator need to figure out the earliest snapshot
2618 // that can see key1:value1_2 is kMaxSequenceNumber, not

2624 callback_finished = true;
2625 };

2627 callback);
2628 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2629

2631 VerifyKeys({{"key1", "value1_2"}});
2632 VerifyKeys({{"key1", "value1_1"}}, snapshot2);
2633 db->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot2);
2634 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();

2690// TODO(myabandeh): how can we be sure that the v2's commit info is evicted
2691// (and not v1's)? Instead of putting a dummy, we can directly call
2692// AddCommitted(v2_seq + cache_size, ...) to evict v2's entry from commit cache.
2693TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, ReleaseSnapshotDuringCompaction3) {
2694 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 7; // same as default
2695 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 1; // commit cache size = 2
2696 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
2697 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
2698 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
2699
2700 // Add a dummy key to evict v2 commit cache, but keep v1 commit cache.
2701 // It also advance max_evicted_seq and can trigger old_commit_map cleanup.
2702 auto add_dummy = [&]() {
2703 auto* txn_dummy =
2704 db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions(), TransactionOptions(), nullptr);
2705 ASSERT_OK(txn_dummy->SetName("txn_dummy"));
2706 ASSERT_OK(txn_dummy->Put("dummy", "dummy"));
2707 ASSERT_OK(txn_dummy->Prepare());
2708 ASSERT_OK(txn_dummy->Commit());
2709 delete txn_dummy;
2710 };
2711
2712 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "key1", "value1"));
2713 auto* txn =
2714 db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions(), TransactionOptions(), nullptr);
2715 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("txn"));
2716 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put("key1", "value2"));
2717 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
2718 // TODO(myabandeh): replace it with GetId()?
2719 auto v2_seq = db->GetLatestSequenceNumber();
2720 ASSERT_OK(txn->Commit());
2721 delete txn;
2722 auto* s1 = db->GetSnapshot();
2723 // Dummy key to advance sequence number.
2724 add_dummy();
2725 auto* s2 = db->GetSnapshot();
2726
2727 // The callback might be called twice, record the calling state to
2728 // prevent double calling.
2729 bool callback_finished = false;
2730 auto callback = [&](void*) {
2731 if (callback_finished) {
2732 return;
2733 }
2734 db->ReleaseSnapshot(s1);
2735 // Add some dummy entries to trigger s1 being cleanup from old_commit_map.
2736 add_dummy();
2737 add_dummy();
2738 callback_finished = true;
2739 };
2740 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack("CompactionIterator:AfterInit",
2741 callback);
2742 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2743
2744 ASSERT_OK(db->Flush(FlushOptions()));
2745 // value1 should be compact out.
2746 VerifyInternalKeys({{"key1", "value2", v2_seq, kTypeValue}});
2747
2748 db->ReleaseSnapshot(s2);
2749 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
2750}

3282 constexpr size_t kNumIterations = 1000;
3283
3284 std::vector<Transaction*> transactions(kNumTransactions, nullptr);
3285 std::vector<size_t> versions(kNumTransactions, 0);
3286 std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string> current_data;
3287 std::vector<const Snapshot*> snapshots;
3288 std::vector<std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string>> snapshot_data;
3289
3290 Random rnd(1103);
3291 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
3292 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
3293
3294 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumTransactions; i++) {
3295 std::string key = "key" + std::to_string(i);
3296 std::string value = "value0";
3297 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), key, value));
3298 current_data[key] = value;
3299 }
3300 VerifyKeys(current_data);
3301
3302 for (size_t iter = 0; iter < kNumIterations; iter++) {
3303 auto r = rnd.Next() % (kNumTransactions + 1);
3304 if (r < kNumTransactions) {
3305 std::string key = "key" + std::to_string(r);
3306 if (transactions[r] == nullptr) {
3307 std::string value = "value" + std::to_string(versions[r] + 1);
3308 auto* txn = db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions());
3309 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("txn" + std::to_string(r)));
3310 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put(key, value));
3311 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
3312 transactions[r] = txn;
3313 } else {
3314 std::string value = "value" + std::to_string(++versions[r]);
3315 ASSERT_OK(transactions[r]->Commit());
3316 delete transactions[r];
3317 transactions[r] = nullptr;
3318 current_data[key] = value;
3319 }
3320 } else {
3321 auto* snapshot = db->GetSnapshot();
3322 VerifyKeys(current_data, snapshot);
3323 snapshots.push_back(snapshot);
3324 snapshot_data.push_back(current_data);
3325 }
3326 VerifyKeys(current_data);
3327 }
3328 // Take a last snapshot to test compaction with uncommitted prepared
3329 // transaction.
3330 snapshots.push_back(db->GetSnapshot());
3331 snapshot_data.push_back(current_data);
3332
3333 ASSERT_EQ(snapshots.size(), snapshot_data.size());
3334 for (size_t i = 0; i < snapshots.size(); i++) {
3335 VerifyKeys(snapshot_data[i], snapshots[i]);
3336 }
3337 ASSERT_OK(db->Flush(FlushOptions()));
3338 for (size_t i = 0; i < snapshots.size(); i++) {
3339 VerifyKeys(snapshot_data[i], snapshots[i]);
3340 }
3341 // Dummy keys to avoid compaction trivially move files and get around actual
3342 // compaction logic.
3343 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "a", "dummy"));
3344 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "z", "dummy"));
3345 ASSERT_OK(db->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
3346 for (size_t i = 0; i < snapshots.size(); i++) {
3347 VerifyKeys(snapshot_data[i], snapshots[i]);
3348 }
3349 // cleanup
3350 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumTransactions; i++) {
3351 if (transactions[i] == nullptr) {
3352 continue;
3353 }
3354 ASSERT_OK(transactions[i]->Commit());
3355 delete transactions[i];
3356 }
3357 for (size_t i = 0; i < snapshots.size(); i++) {
3358 db->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshots[i]);
3359 }
3360}

3436TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, Iterate) {
3437 auto verify_state = [](Iterator* iter, const std::string& key,
3438 const std::string& value) {
3439 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
3440 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3441 ASSERT_EQ(key, iter->key().ToString());
3442 ASSERT_EQ(value, iter->value().ToString());
3443 };
3444
3445 auto verify_iter = [&](const std::string& expected_val) {
3446 // Get iterator from a concurrent transaction and make sure it has the
3447 // same view as an iterator from the DB.
3448 auto* txn = db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions());
3449
3450 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
3451 Iterator* iter = (i == 0) ? db->NewIterator(ReadOptions())
3452 : txn->GetIterator(ReadOptions());
3453 // Seek
3454 iter->Seek("foo");
3455 verify_state(iter, "foo", expected_val);
3456 // Next
3457 iter->Seek("a");
3458 verify_state(iter, "a", "va");
3459 iter->Next();
3460 verify_state(iter, "foo", expected_val);
3461 // SeekForPrev
3462 iter->SeekForPrev("y");
3463 verify_state(iter, "foo", expected_val);
3464 // Prev
3465 iter->SeekForPrev("z");
3466 verify_state(iter, "z", "vz");
3467 iter->Prev();
3468 verify_state(iter, "foo", expected_val);
3469 delete iter;
3470 }
3471 delete txn;
3472 };
3473
3474 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "foo", "v1"));
3475 auto* transaction = db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions());
3476 ASSERT_OK(transaction->SetName("txn"));
3477 ASSERT_OK(transaction->Put("foo", "v2"));
3478 ASSERT_OK(transaction->Prepare());
3479 VerifyKeys({{"foo", "v1"}});
3480 // dummy keys
3481 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "a", "va"));
3482 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "z", "vz"));
3483 verify_iter("v1");
3484 ASSERT_OK(transaction->Commit());
3485 VerifyKeys({{"foo", "v2"}});
3486 verify_iter("v2");
3487 delete transaction;
3488}

3497// Committing an delayed prepared has two non-atomic steps: update commit cache,
3498// remove seq from delayed_prepared_. The read in IsInSnapshot also involves two
3499// non-atomic steps of checking these two data structures. This test breaks each
3500// in the middle to ensure correctness in spite of non-atomic execution.
3501// Note: This test is limitted to the case where snapshot is larger than the
3502// max_evicted_seq_.
3503TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, NonAtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared) {
3504 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 7; // same as default
3505 const size_t commit_cache_bits = 3; // 8 entries
3506 for (auto split_read : {true, false}) {
3507 std::vector<bool> split_options = {false};
3508 if (split_read) {
3509 // Also test for break before mutex
3510 split_options.push_back(true);
3511 }
3512 for (auto split_before_mutex : split_options) {
3513 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
3514 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
3515 WritePreparedTxnDB* wp_db = dynamic_cast<WritePreparedTxnDB*>(db);
3516 DBImpl* db_impl = static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db->GetRootDB());
3517 // Fill up the commit cache
3518 std::string init_value("value1");
3519 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
3520 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), Slice("key1"), Slice(init_value)));
3521 }
3522 // Prepare a transaction but do not commit it
3523 Transaction* txn =
3524 db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions(), TransactionOptions());
3525 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("xid"));
3526 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put(Slice("key1"), Slice("value2")));
3527 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
3528 // Commit a bunch of entries to advance max evicted seq and make the
3529 // prepared a delayed prepared
3530 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
3531 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), Slice("key3"), Slice("value3")));
3532 }
3533 // The snapshot should not see the delayed prepared entry
3534 auto snap = db->GetSnapshot();
3535
3536 if (split_read) {
3537 if (split_before_mutex) {
3538 // split before acquiring prepare_mutex_
3539 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency(
3540 {{"WritePreparedTxnDB::IsInSnapshot:prepared_mutex_:pause",
3541 "AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Commit:before"},
3542 {"AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Commit:after",
3543 "WritePreparedTxnDB::IsInSnapshot:prepared_mutex_:resume"}});
3544 } else {
3545 // split right after reading from the commit cache
3546 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency(
3547 {{"WritePreparedTxnDB::IsInSnapshot:GetCommitEntry:pause",
3548 "AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Commit:before"},
3549 {"AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Commit:after",
3550 "WritePreparedTxnDB::IsInSnapshot:GetCommitEntry:resume"}});
3551 }
3552 } else { // split commit
3553 // split right before removing from delayed_prepared_
3554 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency(
3555 {{"WritePreparedTxnDB::RemovePrepared:pause",
3556 "AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Read:before"},
3557 {"AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Read:after",
3558 "WritePreparedTxnDB::RemovePrepared:resume"}});
3559 }
3560 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3561
3562 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread commit_thread([&]() {
3563 TEST_SYNC_POINT("AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Commit:before");
3564 ASSERT_OK(txn->Commit());
3565 if (split_before_mutex) {
3566 // Do bunch of inserts to evict the commit entry from the cache. This
3567 // would prevent the 2nd look into commit cache under prepare_mutex_
3568 // to see the commit entry.
3569 auto seq = db_impl->TEST_GetLastVisibleSequence();
3570 size_t tries = 0;
3571 while (wp_db->max_evicted_seq_ < seq && tries < 50) {
3572 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), Slice("key3"), Slice("value3")));
3573 tries++;
3574 };
3575 ASSERT_LT(tries, 50);
3576 }
3577 TEST_SYNC_POINT("AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Commit:after");
3578 delete txn;
3579 });
3580
3581 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread read_thread([&]() {
3582 TEST_SYNC_POINT("AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Read:before");
3583 ReadOptions roptions;
3584 roptions.snapshot = snap;
3585 PinnableSlice value;
3586 auto s = db->Get(roptions, db->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key1", &value);
3587 ASSERT_OK(s);
3588 // It should not see the commit of delayed prepared
3589 ASSERT_TRUE(value == init_value);
3590 TEST_SYNC_POINT("AtomicCommitOfDelayedPrepared:Read:after");
3591 db->ReleaseSnapshot(snap);
3592 });
3593
3594 read_thread.join();
3595 commit_thread.join();
3596 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3597 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3598 } // for split_before_mutex
3599 } // for split_read
3600}

3751// Test when we add a prepared seq when the max_evicted_seq_ already goes beyond
3752// that. The test focuses on a race condition between AddPrepared and

3754TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, AddPreparedBeforeMax) {

3756 // This test is only for two write queues

3786 // AddPrepared, t2) update max_evicted_seq_

3799 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
3800 txn_mutex_.Unlock();
3801 });

3808 // invokes AdcanceMaxEvictedSeq

3822 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsNotFound());

3825
3826 read_thread.join();
3827 write_thread.join();
3828 delete txn1;
3829 delete txn2;
3830 ASSERT_OK(txn->Commit());
3831 delete txn;
3832 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3833 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();

3836// When an old prepared entry gets committed, there is a gap between the time
3837// that it is published and when it is cleaned up from old_prepared_. This test
3838// stresses such cases.
3839TEST_P(WritePreparedTransactionTest, CommitOfDelayedPrepared) {
3840 const size_t snapshot_cache_bits = 7; // same as default
3841 for (const size_t commit_cache_bits : {0, 2, 3}) {
3842 for (const size_t sub_batch_cnt : {1, 2, 3}) {
3843 UpdateTransactionDBOptions(snapshot_cache_bits, commit_cache_bits);
3844 ASSERT_OK(ReOpen());
3845 std::atomic<const Snapshot*> snap = {nullptr};
3846 std::atomic<SequenceNumber> exp_prepare = {0};
3847 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread callback_thread;
3848 // Value is synchronized via snap
3849 PinnableSlice value;
3850 // Take a snapshot after publish and before RemovePrepared:Start
3851 auto snap_callback = [&]() {
3852 ASSERT_EQ(nullptr, snap.load());
3853 snap.store(db->GetSnapshot());
3854 ReadOptions roptions;
3855 roptions.snapshot = snap.load();
3856 auto s = db->Get(roptions, db->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key2", &value);
3857 ASSERT_OK(s);
3858 };
3859 auto callback = [&](void* param) {
3860 SequenceNumber prep_seq = *((SequenceNumber*)param);
3861 if (prep_seq == exp_prepare.load()) { // only for write_thread
3862 // We need to spawn a thread to avoid deadlock since getting a
3863 // snpashot might end up calling AdvanceSeqByOne which needs joining
3864 // the write queue.
3865 callback_thread = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread(snap_callback);
3866 TEST_SYNC_POINT("callback:end");
3867 }
3868 };
3869 // Wait for the first snapshot be taken in GetSnapshotInternal. Although
3870 // it might be updated before GetSnapshotInternal finishes but this should
3871 // cover most of the cases.
3872 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency({
3873 {"WritePreparedTxnDB::GetSnapshotInternal:first", "callback:end"},
3874 });
3875 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack("RemovePrepared:Start", callback);
3876 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3877 // Thread to cause frequent evictions
3878 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread eviction_thread([&]() {
3879 // Too many txns might cause commit_seq - prepare_seq in another thread
3880 // to go beyond DELTA_UPPERBOUND
3881 for (int i = 0; i < 25 * (1 << commit_cache_bits); i++) {
3882 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), Slice("key1"), Slice("value1")));
3883 }
3884 });
3885 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread write_thread([&]() {
3886 for (int i = 0; i < 25 * (1 << commit_cache_bits); i++) {
3887 Transaction* txn =
3888 db->BeginTransaction(WriteOptions(), TransactionOptions());
3889 ASSERT_OK(txn->SetName("xid"));
3890 std::string val_str = "value" + std::to_string(i);
3891 for (size_t b = 0; b < sub_batch_cnt; b++) {
3892 ASSERT_OK(txn->Put(Slice("key2"), val_str));
3893 }
3894 ASSERT_OK(txn->Prepare());
3895 // Let an eviction to kick in
3896 std::this_thread::yield();
3897
3898 exp_prepare.store(txn->GetId());
3899 ASSERT_OK(txn->Commit());
3900 delete txn;
3901 // Wait for the snapshot taking that is triggered by
3902 // RemovePrepared:Start callback
3903 callback_thread.join();
3904
3905 // Read with the snapshot taken before delayed_prepared_ cleanup
3906 ReadOptions roptions;
3907 roptions.snapshot = snap.load();
3908 ASSERT_NE(nullptr, roptions.snapshot);
3909 PinnableSlice value2;
3910 auto s =
3911 db->Get(roptions, db->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key2", &value2);
3912 ASSERT_OK(s);
3913 // It should see its own write
3914 ASSERT_TRUE(val_str == value2);
3915 // The value read by snapshot should not change
3916 ASSERT_STREQ(value2.ToString().c_str(), value.ToString().c_str());
3917
3918 db->ReleaseSnapshot(roptions.snapshot);
3919 snap.store(nullptr);
3920 }
3921 });
3922 write_thread.join();
3923 eviction_thread.join();
3924 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3925 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3926 }
3927 }
3928}
